main event: Flashing red and white light observed by military personnel at Williams Bay AFS, Wisconsin, on November 8, 1957.
interesting points: The object was initially stationary, then moved up.
The weather conditions were clear at the time of the sighting.
No known air traffic was reported in the area at the time of the sighting.
The report indicates that the sighting was a 'group observation' by military personnel.
witnesses: Military personnel (A/2C Walter L. Kelly, A/3C Harold Ervin, Capt. Herman Blohm)
